Process of performing callout from Soap API--Outbound
-------------------------------------------------------------

1). Ask end point URL and WSDL file from the external system.
2). create remote site setting and store the end point to authorize the destination domain.
3). https://www.dataaccess.com    : - public url to perfom the soap outbound for poc visit this site.
4). https://www.dataaccess.com/webservicesserver/NumberConversion.wso?WSDL  this web sevice will convert the number to word.
5). Through the above link you will get the wsdl file copy it and paste in the editior and save with extension wsdl.
6). Convert the WSDL to Apex. Setup > Apex Classes > Generate from WSDL > Choose your saved file and click Parse WSDL.
7). Two apex class will be created.
8). call the class based on your requirement. below code for now
9). In munnan org refer the NumberConversionService class.

NumberConversionService.NumberConversionSoap soapClient = new NumberConversionService.NumberConversionSoap();
Long testNumber = 2026; 
try {
    String resultInWords = soapClient.NumberToWords(testNumber); // Invoke the specific SOAP operation method
    System.debug('--- SOAP Outbound POC Success ---');
    System.debug('Input Number: ' + testNumber);
    System.debug('Response From Server: ' + resultInWords); // Expected: "two thousand twenty six"
    
} catch (Exception e) {
    System.debug('--- SOAP Outbound POC Failed ---');
    System.debug('Error Message: ' + e.getMessage());
}


Note: -  {no need of client Id and secret, just parse the wsdl to the apex, if external system provide separately User id and password
		 then update that in the apex class manually }

for now go with this file save it with .wsdl extension.

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<definitions xmlns:tns="http://www.dataaccess.com/webservicesserver/" xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/wsdl/soap/" xmlns:s="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" targetNamespace="http://www.dataaccess.com/webservicesserver/" xmlns="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/wsdl/">
  <types>
    <s:schema elementFormDefault="qualified" targetNamespace="http://www.dataaccess.com/webservicesserver/">
      <s:element name="NumberToWords">
        <s:complexType>
          <s:sequence>
            <s:element name="ubiNum" type="s:unsignedLong" />
          </s:sequence>
        </s:complexType>
      </s:element>
      <s:element name="NumberToWordsResponse">
        <s:complexType>
          <s:sequence>
            <s:element name="NumberToWordsResult" type="s:string" />
          </s:sequence>
        </s:complexType>
      </s:element>
